28/04/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic met with the head of the OSCE Mission to Croatia, Peter Semneby, on Tuesday (27 April). They discussed issues related to Euro-Atlantic integration and the reform process. Roncevic said he had denied allegations the ministry was in any way involved in the detention of returning Serb refugees. He also pledged to submit a ministry report on respect for owners' rights to residential property. He and Semneby discussed NATO's Membership Action Plan as well as the European Commission's positive avis on Croatia's membership bid. (Vecernji List - 28/04/04; HINA - 27/04/04)
